<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Privacy notes for Take Back the Mac."
    />
    <title>Privacy | Take Back the Mac</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="site-header">
      <a class="brand" href="/">
        <span class="brand-mark" aria-hidden="true">TBM</span>
        <span>Take Back the Mac</span>
      </a>
      <nav aria-label="Primary">
        <a href="/manifesto/">Manifesto</a>
        <a href="/#rights">Requests</a>
        <a href="/#idea-form">Add a request</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
      <article class="manifesto-article">
        <header class="article-header">
          <p class="tagline">Privacy</p>
          <h1>No tracking. No selling. No public email list.</h1>
          <p class="lede">
            Take Back the Mac is a small public request board. The privacy goal
            is simple: collect as little as practical, keep emails private, and
            avoid tracking people.
          </p>
        </header>

        <section>
          <h2>What is collected</h2>
          <p>
            If you submit a request, the site stores the request title, details,
            optional name, email address, submission time, and a browser
            generated voter ID used to prevent duplicate submissions and votes.
          </p>
          <p>
            Votes use a random ID stored in your browser. Voting does not
            require an account or email verification.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>What is public</h2>
          <p>
            Request titles, details, vote counts, status, submission date, and
            optional names may appear publicly on the site.
          </p>
          <p>
            Email addresses are not displayed publicly.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>What is not done</h2>
          <p>
            The site does not run analytics, sell email addresses, publish email
            addresses, or use submitted emails for marketing.
          </p>
          <p>
            Email is required only as light abuse prevention and so the project
            can follow up about a submitted request if needed.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Hosting</h2>
          <p>
            The site is hosted on Cloudflare Pages with a Cloudflare D1 database.
            Like any hosted site, Cloudflare may process ordinary request logs
            needed to operate the service.
          </p>
        </section>
      </article>
    </main>

    <footer class="site-footer">
      <span>That's a Mac, Jack.</span>
      <a href="https://paulwelty.com">Started by Paul Welty</a>
      <a href="https://marco.org/2026/04/01/letter-to-john-ternus">Inspired in part by Marco Arment's letter to John Ternus</a>
      <a href="/privacy/">Privacy</a>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
